- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as automated theorem proving is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses a new calculus for conflict resolution, which could be of interest to programming language researchers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a new rule for deriving new clauses. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper introduces a new tool for software verification.
